Description:
Ballistics of 57x348SR caliber UFB-71 HEI-T rounds as fired from various naval gun mounts. Muzzle velocity is increased compared to the ballistics of the S-60 due to lengthened barrel.

Mount   Weapon    Designation  Remarks
ZIF-71  1xZIF-74  N/A          Open, air cooled with water dousing. 160-170 RPM (burst length ~50 rnds), fed by 3 rnd. clips.
ZIF-75  4xZIF-74  N/A          Open, air cooled with water dousing. 130-140 RPM (burst length ~50 rnds), fed by 3 rnd. clips.
ZIF-72  2xZIF-74  AK-725       Enclosed, water cooled, 200 RPM (burst length ~100 rnds), 550 rnd. in disintegrating links. Value is per-barrel. Barrel life 1500 rnd.
A-220   ？        N/A          Enclosed.

Cartridge Loads 1.16kg of 11/7 grains, with geometry:

Geometry         Arch Width    Perforation Diameter  Length
7-perf Cylinder  1.00-1.15 mm  0.45-0.65 mm          11.5-15.5mm

Dimensions:
Barrel Length:        4275   mm
Rifling Length:       3775   mm
Projectile Travel:    3967.5 mm
Chamber Length:        371   mm (breech face to start of rifling)
Occupied by Grain:     298   mm
Chambrage:           1.905
